Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Cut the @courgettes{2} in half lengthways and scrape out the seeds with a #teaspoon{}. Put these 'boats' on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little @olive oil{}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven. Roast for ~{15%mins}. Remove when done and turn the oven up to 200°C. Meanwhile, halve, peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @button mushrooms{1}(chopped into 1cm pieces). Cut the @cherry tomatoes{1}(halved) in half.

Put a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the shallot. Cook for ~{3%mins}. Then add the garlic. Cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the mushrooms to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook until all the liquid has been absorbed back into the mushrooms, ~{5-7%mins}. Take the pan off the heat, add the @crème fraîche{1%pot} and stir through.

Divide the mushroom stuffing between the courgette 'boats'. In a #bowl{} mix the @panko breadcrumbs{15%g} and @hard Italian style cheese{30%g}(grated) together and sprinkle over the stuffed courgettes. Grind on some @black pepper{}. Put on the top shelf of your oven and cook until browned around the edges, ~{15-20%mins}.

Put the cherry tomatoes on another baking tray. Drizzle over a little @oil{} and half the @balsamic vinegar{1%balsamic vinegar}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Place on the middle shelf of your oven. Roast for ~{8-10%mins}.

While the courgettes and tomatoes are cooking, put the rest of the balsamic vinegar in another #mixing bowl{} with a good splash of @olive oil{}. Add the @baby spinach{1} and toss to dress it.

When your courgettes and tomatoes are cooked, take them out of the oven. Add the tomatoes to the spinach, along with any excess oil and balsamic vinegar from the #baking tray{}. Finish with the @sesame sprinkle{25%g} and toss everything together. Serve your stuffed courgettes with some spinach salad on the side. Enjoy!